Sri Lanka  beat England by 69 runs to
even their one-day cricket series at one game apiece.  Mahela Jayawardene scored 144 in 150 balls and Kumar
Sangakara had 69 runs as Sri Lanka reached 309-5 in its 50 overs
after being put in to bat at Headingley in Leeds.  Suranga Lakmal and Suraj Randiv then each took 3-43 as
England was bowled out for 240. Eoin Morgan was top scorer for
the hosts with 52.  The five-match series resumes in two days at Lordâ€™s in
 London , followed by games at Trent Bridge in Nottingham on July
6 and Old Trafford in Manchester on July 9.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
